[[!meta title="Uninstalling Tails using Tails itself"]]

[[!inline pages="doc/first_steps/uninstall.intro" raw="yes" sort="age"]]

You can generally uninstall a Tails USB stick while running Tails from that
same USB stick.

1.  When starting Tails, add the `toram` boot
    option in the *Boot Loader*.

    See [[modifying the boot options using the *Boot Loader*|advanced_topics/boot_options]].

1.  If Tails starts as usual, follow the instructions to [[uninstall Tails
    using Linux|linux]].

    If the system fails to start, the computer might not have enough memory to
    use the `toram` boot option. Try with another computer, uninstall using
    [[another operating system|uninstall]], or uninstall while running Tails
    from another USB stick.
